<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910911-0049</DOCNO><DOCID>910911-0049.</DOCID><HL>   Bankers Trust Is Sued   By GE Unit Over Buy-Out</HL><DATE>09/11/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A3</SO><CO>   BT GE U.MAG</CO><MS>CONGLOMERATES (CGL)CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)FINANCIAL (FIN)</MS><IN>ACCOUNTING (ACC)MAJOR MONEY CENTER BANKS (BAN)ALL BANKS, BANKING NEWS AND ISSUES (BNK)CONGLOMERATES (CGL)HOME ELECTRONICS, FURNISHINGS, APPLIANCES (HMF)</IN><NS>ACCOUNTING AND AUDITING NEWS andamp; ISSUES (ACC)</NS><RE>CONNECTICUT (CT)EUROPE (EU)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- GE Capital Corp. confirmed it has filed suitagainst Bankers Trust New York Corp. over GE Capital's loansto debt-burdened Magnet PLC, a British maker of kitchenfixtures.   The suit, which was filed Sept. 5 in London's High Court,also named the accounting firms Arthur Andersen andamp; Co. andErnst andamp; Young as co-defendants. According to an article inthe newspaper American Banker yesterday, the suit chargedthat GE was misled when it loaned $120 million toward the1989 leveraged buy-out of Magnet. The buy-out was led byBankers Trust.</LP><TEXT>   GE seeks for the loan to rank higher in repaymentpriorities, according to the trade publication. The loan wasGE's first major investment in a British concern. GE Capitalis a financial unit of General Electric Co.   A Bankers Trust spokesman said the claims were &quot;whollywithout foundation.&quot; He added: &quot;Bankers Trust intends tovigorously defend itself against any such proceedings.&quot;   The #629 million ($1.09 billion) management buy-out ofMagnet, which ranks as one of the largest of a public companyin Europe, soured when sluggish demand and high interestrates prevented holders from selling their debt. Industryanalysts estimated that Bankers Trust took a $20 million to$30 million charge on its $100 million buyout loan to Magnet.   Officials at GE Capital and Ernst andamp; Young declined tocomment on the suit. Officials of Arthur Andersen couldn't bereached for comment.</TEXT></DOC>